<p><a href="/people/gerlein-safdi/">Cynthia Gerlein-Safdi</a>, WAVES lab member and PhD student in Civil and Environmental Engineering at Princeton, was named a <a href="https://record.umich.edu/articles/michigan-society-fellows-name-nine-new-members" target="_blank"> Michigan Society Fellow </a> for 2017. Fellows were chosen for the importance and quality of their scholarship and for their interest in interdisciplinary work. During Cynthiaâ€™s tenure at the University of Michigan, she will teach selected courses in her affiliated department - Climate and Space Sciences and Engineering - and continue her  research into the use of radar remotes sensing to characterize the patterns and dynamics of canopy water content. Congratulations, Cynthia!!</p>
